cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Creation (agency relationship is created when):
  (i) Consent: parties expressly or impliedly agree to enter an agency relationship;
  (ii) Control: agent is subject to the principal's control. E.g., agent is at least supervised by principal.
  (iii) Acting on Behalf: the agent must be acting on behalf of the principal, generally meaning the agent acts primarily for the benefit of the principal.
(2) Methods of creation (agency can be created by):
  (i) Agreement by parties: a writing not required;
  (ii) Apparent authority: a principal holds another out as her agent to a third party;
  (iii) Ratification: a principal agrees retroactively to be bound by previously unauthorized acts of an agent.

