cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Termination by parties (agency can be terminated by parties where):
  (i) Party desire: either party manifests to the other the desire to terminate the agency relationship (termination effective when notice is received);
  (ii) Expiration: express terms of the agency expire;
  (iii) Purpose fulfilled: the purpose of the agency relationship has been fulfilled;
(2) Termination by operation of law (can occur where):
  (i) Agent or principal dies;
  (ii) Agent or principal loses capacity;
  (iii) Agent materially breaches a fiduciary duty owed to principal.

