cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Loyalty:
  (i) agent has a fiduciary duty testof undivided loyalty to principal;
  (ii) agent breaches duty if he has adverse interests and fails to disclose such interests;
  (iii) agent cannot act on behalf of two different principals with adverse interests;
(2) Obedience:
  (i) agent must obey principal's lawful instructions;
  (ii) agent's interpretation of principal's instructions must be reasonable under the circumstances;
(3) Care:
  (i) agent must carry out his agency with reasonable care;
  (ii) reasonable care judged in light of local community standards;
  (iii) duty to notify included in duty of care; agent must notify principal of all agency-related matters that come to agent's attention; all such matters are imputed to principal.

