cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Requirements (agent acts with apparent authority if):
  (i) principal holds agent out as having authority to act on principal's behalf;
  (ii) principal's conduct causes a third party to reasonably rely on the agent's appearance of authority;
(2) "Holding out": principal must affirmatively act or fail to act in a way that causes the third party's reasonable belief (mere assertion of authority by agent is insufficient to bind principal);
  (i) Affirmative act: can be words or conduct by principal that causes third party's reasonable belief in agent's authority;
  (ii) Inaction: can be inaction by principal, where a duty to act exists, that causes third party's reasonable belief in agent's authority (e.g., where principal knows third party wrongly believes agent has authority to act, principal has a duty to correct);

