cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Requirements:
  (i) Agent purported to act on principal's behalf: E.g., entered into K with third party without authority to do so;
  (ii) Principal has knowledge of material facts of the act (e.g., K terms): principal must know or reasonably should know of material facts when agent's act is affirmed/ratified;
  (iii) Principal affirmed (i.e., ratified) agent's conduct:
  (a) affirmance can be express or implied (i.e., conduct by principal consistent with approval of the otherwise unauthorized act);
  (b) if principal accepts benefits of the agent's act when it is still possible to decline, principal will be deemed to have ratified agent's act;
(2) Effect of ratification: principal who ratifies an agent's unauthorized act becomes liable to third parties for those acts; E.g., if principal ratifies a K agent unauthorizedly entered into with third party, principal is bound to the K and can be held liable to third party

