cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Third party vs. principal: if agent had authority, principal is liable to the third party;
(2) Third party vs. agent: depends on whether principal is disclosed;
  (i) Disclosed principal: where third party knows of principal's existence and identity then
  (a) principal is liable, agent is not liable;
  (b) only principal, not the agent, can enforce the contract.
  (ii) Undisclosed and/or unidentified principal: both agent and principal are liable to third party and either can enforce the contract.

