cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Analysis-minimum contacts, relatedness, fairness;
(2) Minimum contacts-D must have sufficient minimum contacts with forum state; inquiry focuses on: Purposeful availment-did D avail herself of forum state's laws? Foreseeability-did D know of or anticipate being held accountable for her in-forum activities?;
(3) Fair play & substantial justice (see Cards 6-9)-given D's contacts, exercise of jx must not offend these notions; inquiry focuses on: Convenience-would litigating in the forum severely disadvantage D? State's interest-does forum state have an interest in providing redress for residents or an interest in the outcome?

