cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Relatedness of contacts & claim: does P's claim arise from D's contacts with the forum state?:
  (i) Specific jx: claims arise from D's in-state contacts; Only minimum contacts must be established; D can only be sued for claims arising from in-state contacts;
  (ii) General jx: claims do not arise from D's in-state contacts D has such systematic and continuous contacts that it is essentially "at home" in the forum state (incorporated or place of business in forum state). If found, D can be sued for any claim arising in or outside of forum.
(2) Convenience: would jx in forum severely disadvantage D? E.g., distance to courthouse, inability to travel, or lack of familiarity with court system. Must be so inconvenient and difficult that D is inherently put at severe disadvantage compared to P;
(3) State's interest: Does forum state have an interest in allocating its limited resources to hearing this matter? Interest is less compelling when case involves non-resident actors and non-resident acts or when case involves complexity

