(1) Fed. courts have SMJ over controversies between citizens of different states, even where claims do not involve fed. law;
(2) Diversity jx conferred by Cons and by statute (28 U.S.C.
(1) Complete diversity:
  (i) every P must be of diverse citizenship from every D (i.e., no diversity if any P is citizen of same state as any D);
  (ii) Does not require that all parties be citizens of different states; just no P and no D can be from the same state (e.g., two Ps can be from Utah, as long as no D is from Utah);
  (iii) Examined at time of filing-diversity need not exist when claim arose;
  (iv) Diversity can exist between a citizen of a U.S. state and a foreign country (sometimes called "alienage jx");
(2) Amount in controversy must exceed $75,000: P must make good faith allegation that her claim exceeds $75k.

