cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Lenient standard: to dismiss for insufficient amount, there must be no legal possibility that recovery will exceed $75k. Amount actually awarded is irrelevant.
(2) Equitable relief claims: court looks at value of the harm caused. Can look from either P or D perspective—i.e., does act requiring injunctive relief harm P by more than $75k; or would it cost D more than $75k to comply with the injunction sought?
(3) Aggregating claims: may be permissible to meet $75k requirement. One P can aggregate all her claims against a single D;
(4) Multiple Ps or Ds: aggregating only allowed if either:
  (a) One P has joint liability claims against multiple Ds. Use total value of the claim;
  (b) Multiple Ps seek to enforce a single title or right in which they have a common, undivided interest (rare). E.g., several Ps jointly own real estate and sue D to quiet title—undivided interest, so aggregation OK.

