cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Removal rules:
  (i) Can only remove if the case could have been filed in fed. court;
  (ii) Only D can remove and all Os must agree to removal;
  (iii) Can only remove to the fed. district embracing the state court in which the case was originally filed;
  (iv) D who files a permissive counterclaim in state court waives the right to remove.
(2) Timing: D must remove within 30 days of service of the first removable document (usually service of process);
(3) Procedure: D must file notice in state and fed. courts. Notice must contain grounds for removal and copies of documents served in state court; must be signed; All adverse parties must receive notice of removal;
(4) Diversity jx limitations: D cannot remove if P filed suit in any D's home state; I.e., no removal if any D is a citizen of the forum state;
(5) Remand: If removal is improper, court can remand to state court; Improper procedure - P can move to remand within 30 days; Lack of SMJ - P can move to remand at any time.

