cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Determining proper venue: for most actions venue is proper where
  (i) Any D resides: in any district where any D resides (provided all Ds also reside in the same state in which the district is located);
  (ii) Location of claim or property: in any district in which a substantial part of the claim arose or in which a substantial part of property that is subject to the action is situated;
(2) Residency for venue purposes:
  (i) People: determined by domicile;
  (ii) Corporations: reside in any state where they are subject to PJ. In a state with more than one district, a corporation resides in a district if its contacts would be sufficient to subject it to PJ if that district were a state;
  (iii) Non-corp. business: resident of all districts in which it was subject to PJ when action commenced (broader standard than PPB);
  (iv) Unincorporated associations: residency determined by location of association itself, not individual members

