cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Amendment as a matter of course:
  (i) Within 21 days after service;
  (ii) If the pleading requires a response, within 21 days of service of the responsive pleadings or pre-answer motion (e.g., a Rule 12 motion). E.g., if D answers P's complaint, P has 21 days from service of the answer to amend complaint; Note: Party has 14 days or time remaining on initial 21-day deadline (whichever is longer) to respond to an amended pleading.
(2) Amendment without right:
  (i) Written consent of the adverse party;
  (ii) Leave of court (i.e., court's permission) sought by motion. Leave will be granted freely when justice requires (lenient standard); court looks to:
  (a) Length of and reasons for movant's delay;
  (b) Potential prejudice to parties;
  (c) Futility of amendment.

