cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Effect & terminology: original D becomes a P: Newly joined party is third-party D ("TPD") Original D becomes third-party P ("TPP");
(2) Requirements:
  (i) D may implead a TPD by filing a third-party complaint within 14 days after serving her answer;
  (ii) After 14 days, D must get permission from court;
  (iii) D's claim under impleader must be derivative: D/TPP cannot claim that TPD is solely liable to P; an impleader thus should evaporate once the original P's claim against D fails;
  (iv) Jurisdiction: court must have PJ over impleaded party; court must also have SMJ, and will generally have supplemental jx.
(1) Once TPD is joined, TPD may make claims of her own against other parties as long as SMJ exists over each claim;
(2) Original P may assert claims against TPD arising from the same transaction or occurrence as P's original claims against D/TPP.

