cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Rule 22 interpleader:
  (i) Complete diversity required, meaning stakeholder must be diverse from all claimants; amount in controversy must exceed $75k;
  (ii) SMJ, PJ, and Venue requirements are the same as for any other federal case
(2) Statutory interpleader:
  (i) Diversity requirement, meaning one claimant must be diverse from at least one other claimant; amount in controversy must be $500 or more;
  (ii) Nationwide jx-service is proper on anyone in the U.S.; Venue is proper in any district where any claimant resides;
(3) Example: deceased had life insurance policy with DE corp. having PPB in CA; claimants from NJ, NV, & CA all claim interests. Rule 22 interpleader-improper b/c lack of diversity. Statutory interpleader-proper b/c claimants from different states.

