cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Dismissal without leave of court:
  (i) allowed before D serves an answer or motion for summary judgment ("MSJ");
  (ii) P voluntarily dismisses by filing written notice of dismissal or stipulation signed by all parties who have appeared;
  (iii) Dismissal is without prejudice provided this is the first time that P has dismissed her case;
  (iv) otherwise it is with prejudice;
(2) Dismissal with leave of court:
  (i) required if there has been an answer, motion, or prior dismissal;
  (ii) Court has discretion to grant dismissal on terms and conditions it deems proper;
  (iii) Dismissal is without prejudice unless court states otherwise;
  (iv) Pending counterclaim: if D has filed a counterclaim, P cannot voluntarily dismiss without D's consent.

