(1) Immunity: President has absolute immunity from civil suits arising from official actions taken while in office. No immunity for actions occurring prior to taking office;
(3) Pardon power: President has the power to pardon those accused or convicted of federal crimes (not state crimes);
  (i) Exception: President cannot pardon someone for convictions leading to impeachment;
  (ii) President may also commute sentences;
  (iii) Congress cannot limit President's pardon power.

