cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Exceptions (Const. will apply to private conduct where):
  (i) Exclusive public function: a private entity performs a task traditionally performed by govt. (narrow exception). Arises only if a private entity exclusively operates a govt. function (e.g., private prisons, elections);
  (ii) Significant state involvement (entanglement): govt. affirmatively authorizes or facilitates private conduct;
  (a) State must affirmatively approve or validate private conduct; permitting it alone is insufficient;
  (b) Examples of state action: court enforces a racially restrictive covenant; state provides books to private schools that racially discriminate;
  (c) Examples of no state action: govt. grants liquor license to racially discriminatory private club; private school receiving govt. funds fires a teacher over speech.

