cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Analysis:
  (i) Has there been a deprivation of life, liberty, or property?:
  (a) Liberty deprivation if/when loss of significant freedom of action or freedom provided by Constitution or statute (e.g., institutionalization, government restriction of fundamental rights);
  (b) Property deprivation if/when a legitimate claim or entitlement to a benefit under law, which goes unfulfilled (e.g., public school attendance, welfare);
  (ii) What procedures are required? (determined by balancing):
  (a) Importance of the individual interest involved;
  (b) Value of procedural safeguards to that interest, against
  (c) Government interest (i.e., fiscal or administrative efficiency).
(2) Examples (procedural due process requirements arise with): Terminating welfare/social security benefits; separating child from parents; punitive damages awards; enemy combatant status for citizens obtained in foreign countries.

