cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Application (how EP applies to fed., state, and local govts):
  (i) 14th Amend. EP Clause applies directly to state/local govts.;
  (ii) EP applies to the fed. govt. by incorporation through the 5th Amend. DP Clause (i.e., EP Clause does not apply directly to the fed. govt.);
  (iii) the same analysis and levels of scrutiny apply for EP analysis whether it applies through the 5th or 14th Amend.;
(2) Analysis (if you see anything that could implicate EP, ask):
  (i) Is there a discriminatory classification?: To receive heightened scrutiny, a discriminatory classification must be proved;
  (ii) What level of scrutiny applies given the classification:
  (a) Suspect classifications apply strict scrutiny;
  (b) Quasi-suspect classifications apply intermediate scrutiny;
  (c) All other alleged classifications apply rational basis;
  (iii) Does the classification satisfy the appropriate level of scrutiny?

