(1) The regulation furthers an important govt. interest;
(2) That govt. interest is unrelated to suppression of the message (If the restriction is aimed at speech more than conduct, it is likely unconstitutional);
(3) The impact on speech is no greater than necessary to further the important government interest.
(1) Burning U.S. flag (protected symbolic speech);
(2) Burning a cross (protected unless intended to threaten);
(3) Public nudity (not protected).

