cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Unprotected commercial speech: Test: commercial speech is not protected if it is either:
  (i) False, misleading, or deceptive;
  (ii) Illegal or concerns illegal activity. The govt. may regulate unprotected commercial speech;
(2) Protected commercial speech: speech that concerns lawful activity and is not misleading. Test: govt. can only regulate protected commercial speech if:
  (i) There is a substantial govt. interest in regulating the speech;
  (ii) the regulation directly advances that govt. interest;
  (iii) the regulation is not more extensive than necessary to serve that govt. interest. A valid commercial speech regulation must be narrowly tailored, but not necessarily the least restrictive alternative.

