cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Public figures, public officials, and matters of public concern:
  (i) Public figure = one who has pervasive fame or notoriety or voluntarily assumes a central role in a particular public matter;
  (ii) Public official = public office holder;
  (iii) Matter of public concern = statement relates to a community interest or concern (includes national interests);
(2) Additional requirements: if defamation involves a public figure, official, and/or public concern, P must prove:
  (i) Falsity: P must prove the statement was false;
  (ii) Fault: P must prove D was at fault; standards differ for public vs. private figures;
  (a) Public official or figure uses actual malice standard (knowledge of falsity or reckless disregard as to truth);
  (b) private figure uses negligence of the statement's veracity
(2) Damages:
  (i) Public figures or officials: P can collect compensatory damages and possibly punitive damages;
  (ii) Private figures: damages for actual injury only; P must prove actual malice for compensatory or punitive damages

