cards.backMarkdown:
(1) When a transaction or event is connected to more than one jurisdiction, and the potentially-applicable laws differ, a COL is required to determine which law to apply; 3 approaches (generally states use one of the following COL tests):
  (i) Vested Rights Approach of the First Restatement;
  (ii) Most Significant Relationship Approach of the Second Restatement;
  (iii) Governmental Interest Approach;
(3) Diversity cases:
  (i) a federal court exercising diversity jx over non-federal claims must apply the COL approach of the state in which it sits);
  (ii) For Example: a federal court in State A exercising diversity jx over a tort claim filed by a citizen of State A against a citizen of State B must apply State A's COL approach.

