  (ii) For Example: a federal court in State A exercising diversity jx over a tort claim filed by a citizen of State A against a citizen of State B must apply State A's COL approach.

cards.backMarkdown:
(1) General Rule: Under the First Restatement's Vested Rights Approach, the court applies the law of the forum where the act occurred or the relationship that gave rise to the lawsuit developed; Last act: most often, rights vest in the state where the last act or event occurred that gave rise to the rights being asserted in the lawsuit; Substantive areas of law (depending on the area of substantive law at issue (e.g., tort, contract, etc.), the following usually dictates the forum whose law will apply):
  (i) Torts: court applies law of the forum where the injury occurred (specifically where the last event giving rise to liability occurred);
  (ii) Contracts: court applies law of the forum where the K was formed unless the dispute involves performance; if performance is at issue, court will apply law of the forum in which performance was due;
  (iii) Property: court applies law of the forum where property is located;
  (iv) Tangible property: court applies law of forum where property was located at the time of the relevant transaction;
  (v) Corporations: where issue involves internal corporate affairs (e.g., shareholder dispute), court will apply law of the forum where corporation is incorporated.

