cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: Most Ks are governed by either common law or the UCC;
  (i) Applies to most Ks, except sales of goods;
  (ii) Any K not involving the sale of goods should be treated under common law contract principles;
  (iii) Generally applies to Ks for real estate or services;
(3) UCC Article 2:
  (i) Governs the sale of goods;
  (ii) If both parties to a K are merchants, the UCC has additional special rules (e.g., acceptance with additional terms);
(4) Mixed Ks:
  (i) For Ks involving both goods and services, the predominant purpose of the K dictates the applicable law;
  (ii) Exception: if K terms divide payment between the goods and the services, apply the UCC to the sale of goods portion of the K and common law to the remainder;
(5) Duty of good faith: In both UCC and common law Ks, an obligation of good faith is imposed on the performance and enforcement of a K.

