(1) In General: An offer may be terminated by an act of a party or by operation of law;
  (i) Revocation by offeror;
  (ii) Rejection by offeree;
  (iii) Lapse of time;
  (iv) Offeror can set a time limit for acceptance, at the end of which offeree's power of acceptance automatically terminates;
(3) Operation of law:
  (i) Death or insanity of either party;
  (ii) Destruction of proposed K's subject matter;
  (iii) Supervening illegality.

