cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: Acceptance arises upon offeree's clear expression of assent to the terms of the offer;
  (i) Offeror controls method: offeror is the master of the offer and can dictate the manner by which an offer is accepted;
(2) Mirror Image Rule (common law): acceptance must mirror the offer's terms; it cannot add, omit, or change terms of the offer;
  (i) Acceptance with additional terms: are both parties merchants?
  (a) Yes: K is formed with additional terms unless either:
(1) Additional terms materially change the offer;
(3) Offeror objects within a reasonable time
  (b) No: K is formed, but without additional terms;
(4) Acceptance by shipment (a merchant may accept an offer to buy goods by either):
  (i) Providing a promise to ship goods (usually by written confirmation); or
  (ii) Promptly shipping conforming goods; but
  (iii) Shipment of nonconforming goods acts as an acceptance, but may give rise to breach.

