cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: Offers and acceptances transmitted via mail (however, the mailbox rule does not apply to email) become effective upon either dispatch or receipt;
  (i) Unless otherwise provided, offers invite acceptance in any reasonable manner under the circumstances;
  (ii) For Example: A sends offer to B via e-mail and B accepts via text message; valid K has been formed;
  (iii) If acceptance is via instantaneous two-way communication (e.g., phone), it is treated as if the parties are in each other's presence;
(5) Limitations:
  (i) If the offer stipulates acceptance is not effective until received, the offer controls (i.e., offeror can opt out of mailbox rules);
  (ii) If offeree sends both a rejection and acceptance, first to arrive controls;
  (iii) Option K's: acceptance is effective upon receipt;
(6) Revocation: revocation is effective only upon receipt, and so the mailbox rules do not apply.

