cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: the following are defenses to K formation or enforcement; if established, a court may choose not to enforce an otherwise valid K or it may be void or voidable by parties;
  (i) Incapacity: One or both parties lack capacity to enter into a K;
  (ii) Statute of Frauds (SoF): Ks subject to SoF that fail to meet SoF requirements are invalid;
  (iii) Illegality: Subject matter or purpose of K is illegal;
  (iv) Misrepresentation/Fraud: K that is formed based on fraud or misrepresentation;
  (v) Duress: K that is induced by force, coercion, or duress;
  (vi) Unconscionability: K that is unfair or oppressive to one party;
  (vii) Misunderstanding: Where there is ambiguity concerning terms of a K;
  (viii) Mistake: Where one or both parties is mistaken concerning underlying facts of a K.

