cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: If a contract is within the SoF, it must satisfy SoF requirements to be valid; Contracts within the SoF:
  (i) Marriage Ks: promises made in consideration of marriage;
  (ii) Service Ks incapable of being performed within 1 year:
  (a) SoF does not apply to: "lifelong" deals or Ks that say nothing about time for performance; both are technically capable of performance within one year;
  (iii) Land-related Ks: transfers of property interests, including leases for terms greater than one year;
  (iv) Executor Promises: promises by executors/administrators to personally answer for the debts of the decedent's estate;
  (v) Surety: promises to pay the debt of another;
  (vi) UCC: Sales of goods of $500 or more.

