  (i) Physical: Ks induced by physical duress are void;
  (ii) Non-physical: voidable by the coerced or threatened party;
(5) Unconscionability: courts may refuse to enforce all or part of a K that is unfair or oppressive to one party based on bargaining or terms;
  (i) Arises with adhesion Ks, exculpatory clauses for intentional acts, etc.;
  (ii) Look for an absence of meaningful choice by the disadvantaged party.

