cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: Under UCC Ks, buyer does not officially accept until goods are delivered and she has an opportunity to inspect and/or notify seller;
  (i) Buyer confirms acceptance:
  (a) Buyer, after a reasonable opportunity to inspect the goods, indicates to seller that goods conform or that she will keep them despite nonconformance;
  (b) Payment without an opportunity to inspect is not acceptance;
  (c) If buyer accepts goods, she cannot later reject them;
  (ii) Buyer is silent: buyer fails to reject or notify seller of rejection within a reasonable time;
(3) Revoking acceptance:
  (i) Buyer cannot reject after acceptance unless she discovers a defect;
  (ii) Requirements (buyer can revoke acceptance within a reasonable time after discovering a defect if):
  (a) Defect substantially impairs the goods' value and either:
(1) Buyer accepted goods on the reasonable belief that defect would be cured and it has not been, or
(2) Buyer was excusably ignorant of defect or reasonably relied on seller's assurance that goods conformed.

