(1) In General: If buyer has notified seller of imperfect tender (i.e., delivery of nonconforming goods), seller may have an opportunity to cure; Requirements (seller can cure if):
  (a) Seller gives buyer notice of intent to cure and time for performance has not yet expired: seller must give buyer reasonable notice and deliver conforming good;
  (b) Seller had reasonable grounds to believe nonconforming goods sent would be acceptable: reasonableness is usually based on seller's prior dealings with buyer; seller will have additional reasonable time period to tender conforming goods;

