cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: Material breach occurs when one party's failure to perform under the K substantially deprives the other party of the benefit they bargained for;
  (i) Material breach by one party excuses performance by the other;
  (ii) Materiality of breach is a question of fact;
  (iii) Damages: Recoverable for any breach to the extent they are foreseeable as a probable result of the breach;
(3) Timeliness of performance:
  (i) Failure to perform by the time stated in a K is not a material breach if performance is rendered within a reasonable time after the time stated;
  (ii) Exception: "time is of the essence" clauses;
  (a) If timely performance is essential as stated in the K, failure to perform by that time is a material breach;
  (b) Arises if one party indicates as a term of the K that performance by a given date is essential;

