cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: In an accord and satisfaction, parties to an existing K agree to accept different performance in satisfaction of the original, existing obligation;
  (i) Accord: new agreement to accept alternative performance in lieu of the original performance obligation;
  (a) Consideration: generally required;
(1) Consideration of lesser value: OK if new consideration is either:
  (i) Different than originally bargained-for consideration, To be paid to a third party, or
  (ii) To resolve a good-faith dispute concerning the original K;
  (ii) Satisfaction: performance of the accord agreement; discharges the original K and the accord;
  (iii) Effect of breach: a party may sue under either the original obligation or the accord if there has been no satisfaction.

