  (iii) Creditor TPBs: benefit is conferred based on a debt owed by the promisee to the K;
  (iv) Donee TPBs: benefit is conferred gratuitously.

cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: In order to enforce rights under a K, a TPB's rights must vest; Vesting of rights (occurs when the TPB either):
  (i) Accepts benefits: accepts the benefits of the K in a manner requested by the parties to the K;
  (ii) Sues to enforce: brings suit to enforce the K;
  (iii) Detrimental reliance: detrimentally relies on the K (i.e., materially changes position in justifiable reliance on the K);
(3) Enforcing the K:
  (i) TPB can sue promisor;
  (ii) Promisor can assert any of his own defenses;
  (iii) Promisee can sue promisor at law and in equity for specific performance;
  (iv) Creditor beneficiary can sue promisee on existing obligation between them;
  (v) Donee beneficiary may only sue promisee if detrimental reliance exists.

