cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Revocability:
  (i) Gratuitous assignments may be revocable, however assignments made for consideration are irrevocable;
  (ii) Assignments for consideration: irrevocable;
  (iii) Gratuitous assignments: revocable;
  (iv) Exception (gratuitous assignment is irrevocable if either):
  (a) Obligor has already performed;
  (b) Assignee has received a written claim or tangible object signifying a right to collect (e.g., stock certificate);
  (c) Detrimental reliance by assignee (i.e., estoppel);
(2) Assignee right to sue (assignee can sue):
  (i) Obligor: for non-performance; and obligor can raise any defense to the contract that he could have raised against the assignor;
  (ii) Assignor: for breach of any of the following Assignor's implied warranties, including
  (a) no prior assignment of the same right;
  (b) the right to assign was not subject to defenses;
  (c) no interference with the assigned right.

