cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: In the event of a breach, certain non-monetary remedies (i.e., equitable relief) may be available if money damages are unavailable or inadequate; Specific performance:
  (i) Usually only available for Ks involving real estate or unique goods (e.g., antiques, art);
  (ii) For service Ks, injunctions preventing breach may be available (e.g., injunction enforcing non-compete clause);
(3) Rescission:
  (i) Cancellation of a K;
  (ii) Purpose is to restore parties to their positions before K was made;
  (iii) Often arises where there is mistake, misrepresentation, duress, or some other defense to K enforcement or formation;
(3) Reformation:
  (i) Remedy whereby a K is changed so that it reflects parties' original intent;
  (ii) Can arise where there is a mistake in K formation such that the final K varies from a prior written agreement of parties;
  (iii) Can also arise where K is inaccurate due to some misrepresentation;
(4) Reclamation:
  (i) In UCC Ks, unpaid sellers may stop delivery or reclaim goods from an insolvent buyer;
  (ii) Unpaid seller generally cannot reclaim goods from subsequent buyers.

