cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Breach by seller & buyer keeps goods (depends on if buyer accepts):
  (i) Non-acceptance: damages = fair market value (FMV) of perfectly-delivered goods minus FMV of the goods actually delivered;
  (ii) Acceptance: damages = difference in value between the goods as delivered and the goods as ordered;
  (iii) Note: if seller delivers non-conforming but superior goods, buyer is not responsible for increased value of superior goods;
(2) Breach by seller & seller keeps or buyer returns goods:
  (i) Damages (whichever of the following is higher):
  (a) FMV of goods at the time of breach minus K price, or
  (b) Buyer's costs of covering/replacing goods minus K price;
(3) Breach by buyer & buyer has goods:
  (i) Damages = K price;
  (ii) Arises if goods are: kept by buyer, destroyed after ROL passes to buyer, or returned and seller is unable to resell;
(4) Breach by buyer & seller has goods—either:
  (i) K price minus market price at the time of delivery, or
  (ii) K price minus resale price plus provable lost profits;
(5) Conversion: FMV of goods at the time of the conversion;

