cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Shareholder authority: shareholders exert control over the corp through their power to elect directors, amend bylaws, and approve fundamental changes;
  (i) Directors: shareholders can remove and elect directors;
  (ii) Bylaws: shareholders can adopt, amend, or repeal bylaws;
  (iii) Fundamental changes: shareholders must approve of fundamental changes to the corp structure, which includes
  (a) Mergers;
  (b) Sale of assets outside ordinary business;
  (c) Dissolution;
(2) Inspection rights: shareholders may inspect the corp's books and records for any proper purpose upon written notice;
  (i) Proper purpose: purpose is proper if reasonably related to a person's interest as a shareholder;
  (ii) Notice: five days' written notice must be provided to the corp, and notice must state the proper purpose;
  (iii) Inspection without proper purpose: certain records may be inspected by shareholders regardless of proper purpose, including
  (a) Articles and bylaws;
  (b) Annual reports and meeting minutes;
  (c) BoD resolutions regarding share classifications;
  (d) Corp communications to shareholders.

