cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Meetings (annual and special meetings):
  (i) Annual: corp must hold annual meetings for electing directors and other special matters;
  (ii) Special meetings: may be called to conduct business requiring shareholder approval;
  (iii) Notice required: notice of a meeting must be sent to shareholders eligible to vote;
(2) Voting: unless the articles provide otherwise, each issued share is entitled to one vote;
  (i) Quorum required: quorum must be present for a vote to be cast;
  (ii) Votes: if votes cast within the voting group favoring the action exceed votes cast opposing the action, then action approved;
  (iii) BoD elections: directors are elected by plurality; cumulative voting may be used if allowed by the article;
  (iv) Cumulative voting: each share can cast as many votes as there are BoD vacancies and multiple votes can be cast for one seat (e.g., if five vacancies exist, each share gets five votes);
(3) Proxies: shareholders can vote their shares via proxy executed in writing (i.e., allowing someone else to take their vote);
  (i) Revocability: appointment of a proxy is generally revocable;
  (ii) Exception: proxy appointment is irrevocable if it is coupled with an interest and clearly states that it is irrevocable.

