cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Conflicts of interest: officer/director has a personal interest in some transaction in which the corp is a party;
  (i) Occurs if officer/director knows that he and/or a family member is:
  (a) A party to the transaction;
  (b) Has a beneficial financial interest or is closely linked to the transaction such that it could reasonably be expected to influence how the director/officer votes on the transaction;
  (c) Is affiliated with another entity that is party to the transaction. E.g., is an agent, employee, etc. of the other entity;
(2) Safe harbors (officer/director with a potential conflict of interest in a transaction will not be personally liable if the transaction is either):
  (i) Fair to the corp given circumstances existing at the time; or
  (ii) Approved, after material facts have been disclosed, by either
  (a) Disinterested shareholders, or
  (b) A majority of disinterested board members;
(3) Corporate opportunities: fiduciary duties prevent officers/directors from diverting a business opportunity to themselves where
  (i) corp would have an interest or expectancy in the opportunity; and
  (ii) officer/director does not give corp an opportunity to act first.

