cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Formation: certificate of formation filed with the state; need name of LLC, address of LLC's registered office, and name and address of its registered agent;
(2) Operating agreement:
  (i) governing document, similar to a corp's bylaws; governs relations between members, rights and duties of members and managers, conditions for amending the operating agreement, etc.;
  (i) Management: presumption is that all members manage, but LLCs may also have one or several managers and members;
  (ii) Voting: members or managers may have equal voting rights or may vote in proportion to ownership depending on operating agreement;
  (iii) Distribution rights: similar to corp in that operating agreement dictates how LLC will be managed and profits will be distributed;
(3) Duties (depends on whether members or manager(s) manage):
  (i) Member-managed: all members owe duties of care and loyalty to each other and the LLC;
  (ii) Manager-managed: only managers owe duties of loyalty and care; all members can ratify a manager's act that would violate duty of loyalty;
  (iii) Good faith & fair dealing: all members and managers have an obligation of good faith and fair dealing.

