cards.backMarkdown:
(1) General Rule: D may be held liable if he intends the harm caused, but causes it to a different victim or object than intended:
  (i) Often applies to homicide, battery, and arson;
  (ii) Does not apply to attempt;
  (iii) Defenses and mitigating circumstances may also be transferred;
(2) Effect: under transferred intent, D is usually charged with two crimes:
  (i) Attempt (to commit the originally intended crime);
  (ii) The actual resulting crime;
  (iii) For Example: D intends to shoot A, but kills B; D can be charged with the attempted murder of A and the actual murder of B. Note: merger does not apply b/c there are different victims.

