cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Required elements:
  (i) An agreement between two or more people:
  (a) there needs to be a "meeting of the minds";
  (b) express agreement not required;
  (c) parties do not need to know of each other's existence;
  (ii) Intent to enter into the agreement;
  (iii) Intent to commit the target crime or pursue the unlawful objective;
  (iv) An overt act in furtherance of the target crime:
  (a) not a requirement at common law.
(2) Unilateral vs. bilateral:
  (a) at common law, two or more people must have criminal intent, but MPC allows only one party;
  (b) For Example: under MPC, D may be convicted of conspiracy with another party who was an undercover police officer;
  (c) Unless otherwise instructed, apply common law rule;
(3) Termination: conspiracy ends upon completion of the target crime;
(4) Defenses:
  (i) impossibility is not a defense to conspiracy;
  (ii) withdrawal is generally not a defense to conspiracy but may be a defense to liability for co-conspirators' subsequent crimes.

