cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Co-conspirator liability:
  (i) Each conspirator is liable for co-conspirators' crimes that are:
  (a) Foreseeable;
  (b) Committed in furtherance of the conspiracy
(2) Withdrawal:
  (i) Under common law, one cannot withdraw from the conspiracy itself;
  (ii) MPC allows withdrawal if the withdrawing party thwarts the conspiracy (e.g., by stopping it or notifying police);
  (iii) Subsequent crimes (one can withdraw from co-conspirators' subsequent crimes, including the target offense of the conspiracy):
  (a) Affirmative act required: withdrawal is effective when the withdrawing party makes an affirmative act that notifies his co-conspirators he is withdrawing;
  (b) Must be timely: withdrawal must give enough time for co-conspirators to abandon plans for the target offense;
  (c) The withdrawing party must attempt to neutralize the effect of any assistance he provided to the original conspiracy

