cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Infancy (a defense to criminal liability for minors):
  (i) Under 7 years old, no criminal liability;
  (ii) 7-14 years old, rebuttable presumption against criminal liability;
(2) Diminished capacity (a defense based on D's mental defect):
  (i) Available if D can show that he has some mental defect short of insanity that prevented him from forming the mental state required for the crime;
  (ii) Usually limited to specific intent crimes;
(3) Due process & D's mental condition during trial:
  (i) Due Process Clause forbids D from being tried, convicted, or sentenced if, as a result of his mental disease or defect, D is unable to either:
  (a) Understand the nature of the proceeding, or
  (b) Assist his lawyer in the preparation of his defense;
(4) Capital punishment: D cannot be executed if he is incapable of understanding the nature and purpose of the punishment at the time of execution.

