(1) General Rule: An available defense to criminal liability if a law enforcement agent has induced D to commit a crime
(2) Required elements:
  (i) Criminal design originated with law enforcement: criminal design = idea or plan for the crime;
  (ii) D was not otherwise predisposed to commit the crime:
  (a) D must have had no predisposition to commit the given crime prior to his contact with law enforcement;
  (b) Law enforcement providing an opportunity for a person to commit a crime is not, by itself, entrapment;
  (c) For Example: undercover officer buying drugs from dealer; officer merely provided opportunity for D to make a sale; Note: a very narrow defense; rarely effective because it is negated by any predisposition on D's part; as a result, it is unlikely to be a correct MBE answer.

