cards.backMarkdown:
(1) General Rule: The unlawful killing of another human with malice aforethought; Malice aforethought (arises when no mitigating facts reduce the killing to a lesser crime and D commits the killing with one of the following mental states):
  (i) Intent to kill;
  (ii) Intent to inflict great bodily injury;
  (iii) Depraved/malignant heart: a killing committed with reckless indifference to an unjustifiable risk of human life;
  (iv) Felony murder: killing caused during the attempt or commission of an inherently dangerous or statutorily enumerated felony;
  (a) Intent required (the intent necessary to commit the underlying felony);
  (b) Statutorily enumerated felony (BARKK), statute dictates that a killing resulting from the crime constitutes felony murder;
(3) Causation:
  (i) D's act must be both the actual and proximate cause of the victim's death;
  (ii) Any act by D hastening the victim's death, even if already inevitable, is considered a cause.

