cards.backMarkdown:
(1) False pretenses:
  (i) obtaining title to another's property;
  (ii) using false statements;
  (iii) of past or existing fact;
  (iv) with intent to defraud.
(2) Required elements:
  (i) Obtaining title: obtaining ownership, not mere possession;
  (ii) By false statements: must be an intentional false statement;
  (iii) Of past or existing fact: misrepresentation regarding a future event is not sufficient;
  (iv) Intent to defraud: D must have the intent to steal; victim must be deceived or act in reliance on the false statement in passing title to D;
(3) Larceny by trick:
  (i) obtaining possession;
  (ii) of another's personal property;
  (iii) using false statements of past or existing fact;
(4) Possession vs. ownership is the distinguishing factor:
  (i) Larceny by trick the D acquires possession;
  (ii) False pretenses the D acquires title

