cards.backMarkdown:
(1) General Rule: Creating or altering a written document with purported legal significance to be false, with the intent to defraud; Required elements:
  (i) Creating or altering:
  (a) For Example: drafting, adding, or deleting from a document's contents;
  (b) Also includes offering a forged document as genuine even if D did not create the forged document;
  (ii) A document with purported legal significance:
  (a) A document that carries legal value (e.g., a check or contract, but not a painting);
  (iii) To be false:
  (a) Modifying the document into something it is not;
  (b) Changing its legal significance, not just changing it to be inaccurate;
  (iv) With intent to defraud:
  (a) Specific intent crime;
  (b) Note: actually defrauding somebody is not required; the mere intent to defraud is sufficient.

