cards.backMarkdown:
(1) General Rule: the malicious burning of the dwelling house of another; Required elements:
  (i) Malicious:
  (a) With intent or extreme recklessness;
  (ii) Burning:
  (a) Requires some damage to structure caused by fire;
  (b) Damage from smoke, water, or explosions is not sufficient at common law;
  (ii) Dwelling house:
  (a) Structure where someone lives;
  (b) Common law requirement;
  (c) Note: On MBE it can be a non-residential structure;
  (iii) Of another:
  (a) Another person's house;
  (b) At common law, there can be no arson if you own the dwelling but do not reside there;
  (iv) Damages required:
  (a) Must be charring or something more;
  (b) Discoloration, blackening, or other lesser damage is insufficient.

