cards.backMarkdown:
(1) 4th Amend. only applies if a person has a reasonable expectation of privacy (REOP) regarding the thing or place searched and/or the items seized;
(2) Standing to challenge a govt. search requires a REOP; REOP is determined by the totality of the circumstances:
  (i) No REOP for inherently public things;
  (ii) For Example: No REOP in handwriting, voice, location, odors, public records, things viewable from public space, bank account records, smell of luggage;
  (iii) Areas outside the curtilage are unprotected by the 4th Amend; areas outside one's home and outbuildings are subject to police search and seizure (for example, garbage placed on street);
(4) Automatic standing (REOP always exists if D either):
  (i) Owns, has a right to possess, or lives in the premises to be searched; or
  (ii) Is an overnight guest of the premises to be searched.

