(1) General Rule: If probable cause exists, police may search an entire vehicle (including the trunk) and containers or compartments inside that may contain the evidence they are searching for;
  (i) Police must have probable cause to search the vehicle;
  (ii) Probable cause must arise before the search begins;
(3) Scope of permissible search:
  (i) Police can search entire vehicle and all containers within the vehicle that might contain the object for which they are searching;
  (ii) For Example: police may open packages or luggage that might contain evidence relating to the reason they searched the vehicle;
  (iii) Police may search passengers and their belongings.

