cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Administrative searches:
  (i) govt. agencies may conduct routine searches or inspections of highly-regulated businesses or industries;
  (ii) For Example: building code inspection, inspections for food safety, airline passenger searches;
  (iii) A warrant is required for inspections of private residences or commercial buildings;
  (iv) Requires less particularity than standard warrants;
  (v) A general and neutral enforcement plan for the searches will suffice to validate the warrant;
(2) Public school searches:
  (i) to conduct a search, school officials must have reasonable grounds to believe the search is necessary;
  (ii) Less burdensome standard than probable cause;
  (iii) School search is reasonable if:
  (a) Search offers a moderate chance of finding evidence of wrongdoing;
  (b) Procedure for searching is reasonably related to the objectives of the search;
  (c) Search is not excessively intrusive;
  (iv) Drug tests: random urinalysis is permissible for public school students participating in extracurricular activities.

