cards.backMarkdown:
(1) General Rule: Any person in any proceeding (civil or criminal) may refuse to answer a question if her response might incriminate herself; Privilege only available for compelled testimonial or communicative evidence:
  (i) Testimonial: verbal or otherwise communicative evidence;
  (ii) Lineups and physical evidence: not testimonial;
  (iii) Compelled: elicited or induced;
  (a) evidence produced from D's free will is not compelled (e.g., D's diary is not compelled);
  (b) lie detector tests, custodial interrogations, etc. are compelled and 5th Amend. privilege will apply;
(3) Does not apply to companies:
  (i) a legal entity (e.g., corporation, partnership) has no 5th Amend. privilege against self-incrimination;
(4) Exceptions (privilege does not apply if):
  (i) Grant of immunity: govt. can grant immunity from prosecution for self-incriminating testimony;
  (ii) Incrimination is not possible: for example, statute of limitations has run;
  (iii) Extinguished by waiver: D waives the privilege;

