(1) General Rule (once jeopardy has attached, retrial is still allowed if either:
  (i) Hung jury;
  (ii) Mistrial due to manifest necessity:
  (a) D may be retried when there is a manifest necessity to abort the original trial (e.g., D is too ill to continue);
  (b) If it is discontinued at D's request on grounds not constituting an acquittal;
  (iii) Retrial after a successful appeal by D:
  (a) D can be retried unless the basis for reversal was insufficient evidence to support a guilty verdict;
  (iv) D breaches a plea bargain agreement;
  (v) Separate sovereigns:
  (a) D can be tried for the same crime in different states;
  (b) D can be tried for the same crime in fed. and state court.

