cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Pretrial (preliminary) hearing (may be required to determine if there is probable cause to detain the suspect):
  (i) Required if:
  (a) D is incarcerated or released on bail (i.e., does not apply if D is released on sole condition that she appear for trial);
  (b) There has been no determination of probable cause;
  (c) For Example: Not required if arrest was made with warrant;
  (d) Must occur within 48 hours of detention, if required;
(2) Bail:
  (i) Cannot be higher than necessary to ensure D will appear at trial;
  (ii) Detention without bail is constitutional but a decision to refuse bail is immediately appealable;
  (iii) Arbitrary denial of bail violates due process;
  (iv) For denial of bail, govt. must show either
  (a) D poses a flight risk, or
  (b) D poses a danger to the community.
(3) Right to speedy trial:
  (i) 6th Amend. protects D from unreasonable delay between the time charges are filed and the beginning of trial;
  (ii) Right attaches once D has been arrested or charged;
  (iii) Violations: determined by the totality of the circumstances;
  (iv) Factors: length of delay and reason for delay (e.g., did D cause delay?); if delay has prejudiced D, whether D asserted right;
  (v) Remedy for violation: dismissal of case with prejudice.

