cards.backMarkdown:
(1) General Rule: 6th Amend. gives D the right to confront adverse witnesses; Confrontation:
  (i) D has a right to have adverse witnesses testify in-person and subject to cross-examination;
  (ii) In-person testimony not required if
  (a) exclusion is necessary for public policy;
  (b) reliability of the testimony is otherwise assured;
  (iii) D can be removed from court for disruptive behavior;
(3) Co-defendant confessions:
  (i) a co-D's confession implicating D is inadmissible against D at a joint jury trial (OK at bench trial);
  (ii) Exceptions (confession of a co-D is admissible if either):
  (a) Confessing co-D testifies subject to cross-examination;
  (b) Ds have separate trials;
  (c) Confession is redacted so that all portions referring to the co-D are eliminated;
  (d) Co-D's confession is used to rebut D's claim that his confession was obtained coercively;
(4) Hearsay:
  (i) prior testimonial statements of unavailable witnesses are only admissible if D had the opportunity to cross-examine the declarant when the statement was made.

