cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Methods of impeachment:
  (i) Contradiction;
  (ii) Prior inconsistent statement (PIS);
  (iii) Bias or interest;
  (iv) Sensory deficiencies (E.g., W's senses were incapable of producing the perceptions to which W testified);
  (v) Reputation and/or opinion of untruthfulness (Admissible to impeach W's veracity by use of extrinsic evidence);
  (vi) Prior acts of misconduct;
  (vii) Extrinsic evidence is prohibited;
  (viii) Prior criminal conviction;
(2) Evidence supporting witness credibility:
  (i) inadmissible unless credibility has been attacked (i.e., W has been impeached);
  (ii) Exception: W's prior consistent statement is admissible if the statement was made before W had a motive to fabricate.

