  (i) Establishing PIS: may be established through cross-exam or extrinsic evidence; Extrinsic evidence is inadmissible if the PIS relates to a collateral matter;
  (ii) Foundation requirement: W must have an opportunity to explain or deny the statement; not required for PIS by a hearsay declarant;
(3) Prior inconsistent statements & hearsay:
  (i) if PIS is hearsay, it is admissible for impeachment purposes, but inadmissible as substantive evidence (to prove the truth of the matter asserted);
  (ii) For Example: a hearsay PIS may only be considered for its bearing on W's credibility;
  (iii) If the PIS is not hearsay or it falls under a hearsay exemption/exception, it may be considered for any purpose

