  (i) W may be questioned on cross-exam about any prior misconduct probative of truthfulness (i.e., lying or deceit);
  (ii) Arrests does not equal misconduct; must be an act of lying;
  (iii) No extrinsic evidence permitted: W may only be asked about prior misconduct; questioning attorney must accept W's answer
(3) Impeachment based on opinion or reputation for untruthfulness: W may be impeached by testimony describing his reputation for untruthfulness in the community.

