cards.backMarkdown:
(1) "Statement": an oral or written assertion, or non-verbal conduct intended as an assertion;
  (i) Non-human assertions are not statements (e.g., test results, radar gun reading, dog barking);
  (ii) Out-of-court statements are not hearsay if offered to prove anything other than the truth of the matter they assert;
(2) Exemptions vs. exceptions: (fed. rules create both exceptions and exemptions to the hearsay ban):
  (i) Exemptions: deemed "non-hearsay" and thus admitted;
  (ii) Exceptions: deemed hearsay, but still admitted;

