cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Requirements (former testimony is admissible if):
  (i) Declarant is currently unavailable;
  (ii) Declarant's prior testimony was given under oath;
  (iii) Party against whom testimony is now offered was either:
  (a) A party in the previous action and had an opportunity to cross-examine declarant;
  (b) Motive for cross-examining declarant in former hearing must be similar to the current motive;
  (c) A predecessor in interest of a party in the previous action, in which there was an opportunity to cross-examine declarant and a similar motive for doing so;
  (d) Predecessor in interest is one who has a close privity-type relationship with the party in the earlier proceeding;
  (iv) Applicable in civil actions only;

