(1) Requirements (statement admissible if):
  (i) Declarant is currently unavailable (death of declarant is not required);
  (ii) The out-of-court statement was made under the belief of impending death (the declarant must only have believed he was dying when the statement was made);
  (iii) The statement was made regarding the cause or circumstances surrounding the belief of impending death;
(2) Only available in:
  (i) Civil cases;
  (ii) Homicide cases.

