(1) Requirements:
  (i) Statement must be made to medical personnel. "Medical personnel" includes anyone involved in treatment or diagnosis; not necessarily a doctor;
  (ii) Statement must be pertinent to assisting in the diagnosis or treatment of a condition:
  (a) Related statements (such as an admission) about an injury-causing event are usually inadmissible;
  (b) For Example: statement by declarant to an emergency room doctor that she was shot will be admissible, but the identity of the shooter will not, as it is not pertinent to treatment;
  (iii) Distinguish from statements of then-existing physical condition: statements concerning then-existing (i.e., contemporaneous) physical condition are admissible regardless of whether they are made to medical personnel.

