cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Learned treatises:
  (i) Arises with expert testimony only;
  (ii) Learned treatises are accepted authority in a given field;
  (iii) Established as reliable and accepted authority by testimony, admission, or judicial notice;
  (iv) Experts can rely on learned treatises on direct exam or can be impeached with information from treatises on cross-exam;
  (v) If admissible, statements from learned treatises may only be read into evidence;
(2) Family records: statements of fact found in family keepsakes, e.g., jewelry engravings, genealogies;
(3) Ancient documents: a form of documentary evidence.

