cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Out-of-court statement offered against D will be excluded if:
  (i) The declarant is currently unavailable;
  (ii) D had no prior opportunity to cross-examine the declarant about the statement at the time it was made;
  (iii) The statement is testimonial;
  (iv) Exception: an out-of-court statement will not be excluded if declarant is unavailable as a result of D's own wrongdoing;
(2) Testimonial statement (includes):
  (i) Prior statements made during court proceedings;
  (ii) Statements made in furtherance of a police investigation (for example, a statement aimed at producing evidence potentially relevant to a later prosecution);
  (iii) Business records are not generally considered testimonial;
  (iv) Exception: statements made to police during an ongoing emergency are non-testimonial and can be admitted without violating the Confrontation Clause.

