cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: A fee simple estate that automatically terminates and reverts back to the grantor upon the happening of a given event or condition; For Example: "to A for so long as he practices law"; if A stops practicing law, property automatically reverts back to grantor; Characteristics:
  (i) Automatic forfeiture: upon occurrence of the given event or condition, the grantee automatically forfeits the estate;
  (ii) Potentially infinite: duration can be infinite so long as the event or condition does not occur;
  (iii) Transferable: the fee estate is alienable, devisable, and descendible, subject to the condition;
(2) Creation: requires clear durational language; words of desire, hope, or aspiration are insufficient; Accompanying future interest is a possibility of reverter: Grantor retains a possibility of reverter; after the property may revert back to grantor, but only if the event or condition occurs.

