cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: If tenant breaches his leasehold duties, landlord's options depend on whether tenant retains possession (i.e., remains on premises); Tenant retains possession (landlord may):
  (i) File for notice of eviction,
  (ii) Continue the lease and sue for rent due;
(3) Tenant abandons premises (landlord may):
  (i) Surrender: treat the abandonment as tenant's surrender and accept it, releasing the tenant from the lease;
  (ii) Ignore (minority rule): hold tenant liable for unpaid rent;
  (iii) Re-let (majority rule): lease premises to new tenants and hold the breaching tenant liable for any losses;
(4) No self-help: landlord may not engage in self-help upon tenant's breach (for example, forcibly removing tenant or tenant's belongings, changing locks, etc.);

