(2) Requirements (acquirer's use of another's land must be):
  (i) Continuous: for the applicable statutory period;
  (ii) Open and notorious: owner knows or should know of use;
  (iii) Actual;
  (iv) Hostile: without owner's permission;

cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: An easement legally implied based on prior use by a common grantor on land subsequently divided into multiple plots; Requirements:
  (i) Easement exists prior to division of a single tract of land;
  (ii) Common grantor's use is continuous and apparent;
  (iii) Use is reasonably necessary for enjoyment of the dominant tenement;
  (iv) Parties intended the use to continue after division of the land;
(3) Exceptions (easement may be implied without prior use where):
  (i) Subdivision plat: lots in a subdivision are sold with reference to a map plan;
  (ii) Profit à prendre: holder of a profit à prendre has an implied easement to pass over the land's surface as reasonably necessary to extract materials (e.g., wood, coal).

