cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: entitles the holder to prevent the servient landowner from engaging in otherwise permissible actions on his own land; Four categories of acts may be prevented:
  (i) Light;
  (ii) Air;
  (iii) Subjacent or lateral support;
  (iv) Stream of water from an artificial flow;
(2) Creation: can only be created by express grant (writing signed by grantor); Note: restrictive covenants are utilized more frequently than negative easements to prevent a landowner from engaging in certain activities on their land.

