cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: A promise to do or refrain from doing something related to land; a contractual limitation or promise regarding land;
  (i) Note: covenants are not property interests;
(2) Real covenant: a covenant concerning real property;
  (i) Runs with the land at law: subsequent owners may be burdened by the covenant or may enforce it;
  (ii) Different requirements apply for burdens and benefits running with the land;
  (iii) Affirmative covenant: a promise to do something related to land;
  (iv) Restrictive covenant: a promise to refrain from doing something related to land;
(3) Termination (can occur by):
  (i) Written release;
  (ii) Merger of benefited and burdened estates;
  (iii) Condemnation of burdened property;
(4) Covenants vs. equitable servitudes (difference is the remedy):
  (i) Covenant: money damages;
  (ii) Equitable servitude: injunction.

