cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: a successor in interest to the burdened estate will be bound by a covenant if the requirements below are satisfied;
  (i) Writing: original covenant was in writing;
  (ii) Intent: parties intended to bind successors in interest; look to language of the covenant; courts are liberal in construing requisite intent;
  (iii) Touches and concerns the land: covenant must affect parties' legal relations as landowners (a very low standard); homeowner association fees satisfy this requirement;
  (iv) Horizontal and vertical privity: must exist between interested parties;
  (a) Horizontal privity: relationship between the covenanting parties (for example, grantor/grantee, landlord/tenant, fee ownership/easement right in same land, mortgagor/mortgagee);
  (b) Vertical privity: relationship between covenanting parties and their successors in interest (for example, contract, devise, descent);
  (v) Notice: successor in interest had notice of the covenant when she took her interest.

