cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: A successor in interest to the benefiting estate may enforce the covenant if the requirements below are satisfied.
(2) Requirements:
  (i) Writing: original covenant was in writing;
  (ii) Intent: original parties intended benefit to run with land; look to language of the covenant; courts are liberal in construing requisite intent;
  (iii) Touches and concerns the land: the covenant must affect parties' legal relations as landowners (a very low standard);
  (iv) Vertical privity: successors in interest are in vertical privity with the original covenanting parties (e.g., through contract, devise, or descent); can be relaxed (not full) for the burden to run; horizontal privity is not required for majority of states.

