cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General:
  (i) Equitable servitudes are covenants enforced in equity against successors through injunctive relief (i.e., injunction is the remedy);
  (ii) This is a covenant that will be enforced against successors of the burdened land who have notice of the covenant;
  (iii) Privity is not required to bind successors;
(2) Creation (requirements):
  (i) Writing: written promise; Exception: reciprocal negative servitudes may be implied from a common scheme for development of a residential subdivision;
  (ii) Intent: original parties must intend to bind successors;
  (iii) Touches and concerns the land;
  (iv) Notice: successors of the burdened land had notice; notice not required for benefit to run;
  (v) Defenses to enforcement (a court will not enforce an equitable servitude if any of the following conditions exist):
  (a) Pervasive changes in the neighborhood;
  (b) Estoppel;
  (c) Acquiescence;
  (d) Unclean hands;
  (e) Laches.

