cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: If land is subdivided into parcels under a common development scheme, with only some parcels having negative servitudes, these restrictions may be impliedly binding against all subdivided parcels; Purpose: Allows lot owners to enforce restrictions on the use of property against other subdivision lot owners (enforced through injunction); Note: usually arises on exam where an owner divides land into smaller lots to create a common development scheme/subdivision; this is a "reciprocal negative easement" or "implied reciprocal servitude." Created through implication if:
  (i) Common scheme: developer evidenced intent to create a negative servitude under a common scheme for all subdivided parcels;
  (a) Common scheme may be evidenced through: recorded plat; general pattern of restrictions; and/or oral representations to early buyers;
  (ii) Notice: owner of the subject lot had notice of the restriction in the deeds of other subdivision lots;
  (a) Notice may be one of three types:
(1) Actual: literal knowledge of restriction;
(2) Inquiry neighborhood character indicates a common restriction;
(3) Record: chain of title for the owner's lot includes a prior deed containing a negative covenant/servitude.

