(5) Leasing: adverse possessors can lease a portion of the land to a third party and still possess the property;
(6) Non-marketable title: title taken by adverse possession is not marketable, unless there has been an action to quiet title.

cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Tacking: adverse possessors can tack together successive periods of adverse possession to satisfy the statutory period, even if successive possession was by different adverse possessors;
  (i) Must be successive: there cannot be gaps between periods of adverse possession;
  (ii) Privity: requires privity between successive adverse holders; satisfied if subsequent possessor takes by descent, devise, or by deed purporting to convey title; tacking not permitted if one adverse claimant ousts the preceding claimant;
(2) Concurrent owners: co-tenants may not adversely possess each others' interests unless ouster has occurred; to adversely possess a co-tenant, the co-tenant must be excluded from the land for the statutory period; the statutory period begins once exclusion begins.

