cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Special use permit: certain property uses require a special use permit even where zoning generally allows the type of use (e.g., hospitals and drive-thrus in commercial zoning districts);
  (i) Condition for govt. approval of a new development;
  (ii) Condition is usually a payment or gift of property to govt. to offset the development's demands on public services;
  (iii) For Example: due to population increase from a new housing development, govt. will have to install new bus stops and traffic lights in surrounding areas—govt. can seek some exaction (for example, payment) from developer;
(3) Requirements (exactions are unconstitutional unless they satisfy the following):
  (i) Nexus: there must be a rational relationship (nexus) between the exaction sought by the govt. and the burden on public facilities;
  (ii) Proportionality: exaction must reasonably relate, in nature and scope, to the impact of the development.

