cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: UCC Art. 9 applies to any transaction intended to create a SI in property or fixtures; Exceptions (Art. 9 does not apply to certain transactions, notably):
  (i) Transactions governed by fed., state, or foreign law;
  (ii) Most real property transactions involving interests or liens on land (i.e., does not apply to mortgages on real property);
  (iii) Assignment of tort claims (except with respect to proceeds and priority in proceeds from tort claims);
  (iv) Assignment of claims for wages;
(3) Secured transactions vs. contracts:
  (i) Contract law and UCC Art. 2 are about rules governing transactions of goods and services;
  (ii) Secured transactions and UCC Art. 9 are about protecting or securing the exchange of goods or services, not the rules governing how one can make such an exchange.

