cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In some transactions, SIs are perfected automatically once attached; automatic perfection occurs with the following:
  (i) PMSI in consumer goods:
  (a) PMSI arises where a creditor sells goods to debtor and/or advances funds to debtor to buy goods, reserving a SI in the goods themselves;
  (b) For Example: A sells B a TV on credit; once the SI is created and attached (i.e., when B receives the goods), A has a PMSI in goods that is automatically perfected;
  (c) Consumer goods only: automatic perfection only occurs for PMSIs in consumer goods; a PMSI in inventory or equipment must be filed to be perfected;
  (d) Limitation: motor vehicles (notation on the vehicle title) and fixtures (require fixture filing);
  (ii) Small assignment of accounts (SI perfects automatically when):
  (a) Accounts or payment intangibles are assigned;
  (b) Assignment does not transfer a significant portion of the assignor's outstanding accounts or intangibles;
  (iii) Sale of payment intangibles or promissory notes: automatically perfected.

