cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: almost any Secured Transaction MEE question will involve issues of priority; note type of collateral involved (goods, inventory, livestock, equipment, etc.); and type of parties involved (secured party vs. secured party, secured party vs. unsecured party, secured party vs. lien creditor, etc.); Priority between parties:
  (i) Attached vs. unattached/unsecured interest: attached SI prevails; Note: beware of scenarios where someone signed a security agreement but has not given value or has no rights in the collateral;
  (ii) Perfected vs. unperfected SI: Perfected SI prevails; applies even if perfected party takes interest with knowledge of earlier unperfected interest;
  (iii) Perfected vs. perfected SI:
  (a) First to file or perfect prevails;
  (b) When there are conflicting perfected SIs, priority goes to party that first filed or perfected (usually will be first to file);
  (c) Where collateral is not subject to filing requirements (or cannot be filed), first to perfect obtains priority;
  (d) knowledge of a prior unperfected SI will not prevent a prospective secured party from filing first to obtain priority.

