(1) In General: Perfected SIs in proceeds generally have the same date of priority as the SI in the original collateral that generated the proceeds; Proceeds from varying categories of collateral (where multiple SIs exist in proceeds, the type of collateral that generated the proceeds can determine priority):
  (i) Filing collateral: secured party would normally achieve priority by filing financing statement (for example, goods, accounts, general intangibles);
  (ii) Non-filing collateral: secured party would normally achieve priority by possession or control, not filing (for example, cash, chattel paper, negotiable documents, instruments).

