cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Fixtures (goods that become attached to real property, such that an interest in them arises under real property):
  (i) Priority: first to file or record prevails;
  (ii) Where a SI in fixtures competes again an interest in the real property containing the attached fixture, the first party to file a fixture filing or record its real property interest prevails;
  (iii) Fixture filing: filing a financial statement where the mortgage on the real property would be recorded;
  (iv) Exception: PMSIs;
  (v) PMSI secured parties who make a fixture filing within 20 days of affixation prevail over a real property interest recorded prior to affixation;
(2) Accessions (collateral that does not lose its identity when physically united with other goods):
  (i) For Example: hard drive serving as collateral does not lose its identity when installed in a laptop;
  (ii) SIs can be created in the collateral and continue when collateral becomes an accession;
(3) Crops: Perfected SI in crops has priority over an interest in the land on which crops are planted, regardless of time of filing or perfection.

