cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Governing law (the law of the state where debtor is located generally governs perfection of a SI):
  (i) Individual debtors: location is place of principal residence;
  (ii) Registered organizational debtors: location is state under whose laws it is organized (for example, where Articles of Incorporation filed);
  (iii) Unregistered organizational debtors (for example, partnership): location is place of business or chief executive office if more than one place;
(2) Common exceptions:
  (i) Certificate of title: where goods are covered by a certificate of title (e.g., automobile), the state issuing the most recent certificate of title governs perfection;
  (ii) Agricultural liens: governed by law of state in which farm product is located;
  (iii) Possessory SIs: governed by law of state in which collateral is located.

