cards.backMarkdown:
(1) General Rule: An intentional harmful or offensive contact to P's person by D; Elements:
  (i) Harmful or offensive contact by D;
  (a) Harmful contact is contact that causes pain, injury, etc.;
  (b) Contact is offensive if it would be considered offensive by a reasonable person and P has not consented;
  (ii) To P's person;
  (a) Includes anything closely connected to P's person (e.g., P's hat);
  (iii) Intent;
  (iv) Causation;
  (a) Indirect contact is sufficient—i.e., causing the force that gives rise to harmful or offensive contact;
  (b) For Example: greasing a floor so that P will slip and fall.

