cards.backMarkdown:
(1) General Rule: An intentional act by D resulting in P's restraint or confinement to a bounded area; Elements:
  (i) Act (or omission) resulting in P's restraint or confinement;
  (a) Restraint or confinement does not have to be physical;
  (b) For Example: can be threats of force, invalid use of legal authority;
  (c) Duration is not important; brief confinement will suffice;
  (ii) P is confined to a bounded area;
  (a) P must be aware of or harmed by the confinement;
  (b) P's freedom of movement must be limited;
  (c) P must not be aware of any reasonable means of escape;
  (d) If a reasonable person could get out (e.g., by opening an unlocked door), no false imprisonment;
  (iv) Causation;
  (v) Shopkeeper's privilege (a store may detain a suspected thief if):
  (a) Store has reasonable cause to believe a theft occurred;
  (b) Store detains suspect in a reasonable manner (only non-deadly force is permitted) for purposes of investigation;
  (c) Detention is reasonable in length and scope;

