cards.backMarkdown:
(1) General Rule: Extreme and outrageous conduct by D causing P's severe emotional distress;
  (i) Extreme and outrageous conduct by D;
  (a) Conduct that exceeds the bounds of decency in society;
  (b) Mere insults alone are insufficient;
  (c) Conduct must be outrageous to a reasonable person unless:
(1) D targets P's known sensitivity or weakness; D's conduct is continuous or repetitive; D targets a P who is a member of a "fragile" class (e.g., elderly, children, pregnant women); or
(4) D is a common carrier or innkeeper
(2) Severe emotional distress in P;
  (a) P must suffer severe emotional distress from D's conduct;
  (b) Physical symptoms are not necessary;
(3) Intent or recklessness: Recklessness when D disregards the likely consequences of his acts;

