cards.backMarkdown:
(1) General Rule: When D's conduct is directed at a third person and P (the bystander) suffers severe emotional distress, P must prove the same IIED elements with additional intent and causation requirements;
(2) Elements:
  (i) Extreme and outrageous conduct by D;
  (ii) severe emotional distress in P;
  (iii) Intent or recklessness;
  (iv) Causation.
(3) Additional requirements:
  (i) P was present at the time;
  (ii) P was a close relative of TP, or distress resulted in bodily harm;
  (iii) D knew these facts;
(4) Note: P does not need to establish additional requirements if P proves D had a design or purpose to cause severe distress to P.

