cards.backMarkdown:
(1) General Rule: D has a legal privilege to use peaceful means to recover possession of chattel taken unlawfully, and to use reasonable, non-deadly force if in fresh pursuit of the chattel-taker;
  (i) also a defense to assault and battery and false imprisonment;
(2) Limitations & requirements:
  (i) D-owner must make a timely demand for return of chattel;
  (ii) Exception:
  (a) Not required if making demand would be futile or dangerous;
  (b) D-owner may recapture from original wrongdoer or a third person who knows the chattel was wrongfully obtained;
  (c) Recapture is not available if chattel is in the hands of an innocent party;
(3) Use of force:
  (i) Reasonable force may be used to recapture chattel only if in fresh pursuit of one who has wrongfully obtained possession;
  (ii) No deadly force or serious bodily harm permitted.

