cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Malicious prosecution: D initiates a frivolous charge or claim against P with an improper purpose (e.g., filing a false police report); Elements:
  (i) D commenced a prior criminal or civil legal proceeding against P (Note: prosecutors are immune);
  (ii) Prior proceeding terminated in P's favor;
  (iii) No probable cause for the original proceeding; (for example, D knew P was not guilty (criminal) or liable (civil) or had insufficient facts to reasonably believe in P's guilt or fault);
  (iv) D had an improper purpose in initiating the proceeding;
  (v) Damages;
(1) Abuse of process: D uses the legal system as an ulterior purpose to threaten or act against P; Elements:
  (i) Wrongful use of process for an ulterior purpose;
  (ii) Definite act or threat against P to accomplish an ulterior purpose.

