cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Intentional Misrepresentation (fraud, deceit); Elements:
  (i) D misrepresents a past or present material fact;
  (ii) D knows or believes the misrepresentation is false;
  (iii) D intends to induce P to act or refrain from acting in reliance on the misrepresentation;
  (iv) Actual reliance by P (causation, P must actually rely on the misrepresentation);
  (v) Justifiable reliance by P (P must be justified in relying on the misrepresentation);
  (vi) Damages: P must suffer monetary loss;
(1) Negligent Misrepresentation; Elements:
  (i) D misrepresents a past or present material fact in a business or professional setting;
  (ii) Breach of duty of care owed to a particular P (i.e., D knew P could rely on the misrepresentation);
  (iii) Actual and justifiable reliance by P;
  (iv) Damages: P must suffer monetary loss.

