cards.backMarkdown:
(1) General Rule: D owes a duty of care, to behave like a reasonably prudent person, to all foreseeable plaintiffs in the zone of danger;
  (i) Reasonably prudent person (RPP);
  (ii) D's duty is to behave like a reasonably prudent person under the circumstances;
  (iii) RPP is considered to be someone with D's physical characteristics, but with the knowledge and mental capacity of an ordinary person;
(3) Foreseeable victims:
  (i) Those within the zone of danger;
  (ii) Zone of danger: the area around D's activities in which a P could foreseeably be injured;
  (iii) Rescuer's exception: if D puts himself or another in danger and a third person attempts to rescue, D can be held liable for the rescuer's injuries, even if unforeseeable;
  (iv) Does not apply to emergency personnel (e.g., firefighters or police) if their injury results from a risk inherent to the job;
  (v) Prenatal injury: a duty of care is owed to a viable fetus.

