cards.backMarkdown:
(1) General Rule: D breaches his duty when his conduct falls short of the standard of care owed under the circumstances;
  (a) RPP standard;
  (b) Negligence per se;
  (c) Specialized standard of care;
  (d) Custom or usage in an industry (not an automatic breach, but may be relevant);
(3) Res ipsa loquitur:
  (i) The very occurrence of the accident causing P's injuries suggests negligent conduct;
  (ii) Arises if facts cannot establish breach of duty b/c circumstances surrounding the event are unknown to P;
(4) Requirements (P must show):
  (i) Inference of negligence: the harm would not normally occur absent negligence;
  (ii) Attributable to D: this type of harm normally results from negligence by one in D's position;
  (iii) Often satisfied by showing that the injury-causing instrument was in D's exclusive control;
  (iv) Injury was not attributable to P.

