cards.backMarkdown:
(1) In General: Under strict liability, D has an absolute duty to make activities safe; Allows P to establish D's liability for P's injuries without proving D acted negligently;
(2) Strict liability is limited to cases involving:
  (i) Ultrahazardous and/or abnormally dangerous conditions;
  (ii) Animal conduct;
  (iii) Products liability;
(3) Prima facie case:
  (i) Nature of D's activity imposes absolute duty to make safe;
  (ii) Causation:
  (a) actual and proximate cause;
  (b) Dangerous aspect of D's activity caused P's injury;
  (d) D generally liable only to foreseeable Ps;
  (iii) Damages to P's person or property;
(4) Note: no amount of due care will relieve D of liability under strict liability;
(5) Defenses: Assumption of risk, comparative negligence.

