cards.backMarkdown:
(1) General Rule: Abnormally dangerous or ultrahazardous activities or conditions give rise to strict liability for any resulting injuries;
(2) Requirements (abnormally dangerous activity/condition exists if):
  (i) Severe risk: condition or activity imposes a severe risk of harm to persons or property;
  (ii) Cannot be made safe: it cannot be made reasonably safe; cannot be performed without a serious risk of harm;
  (iii) Uncommon: condition or activity is uncommon in the community (Note: often arises on the MBE with explosive, toxic, and/or biohazardous materials);
(3) Injury must result from the abnormally dangerous activity:
  (i) Watch for fact patterns where abnormally dangerous conditions exist, but do not cause P's injury;
  (ii) For Example: truck carrying toxic waste in sealed containers, which fall and crash into P's car but do not spill;
  (iii) No strict liability b/c the abnormally dangerous nature of the containers did not cause P's injury.

