cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Manufacturing defect:
  (i) Product departs from its intended design, causing it to be more dangerous than all of the manufacturer's other products of same kind;
  (ii) Requirements: P must show that the product failed to perform as safely as an ordinary consumer would expect;
(2) Design defect:
  (i) Product creates an unreasonable risk of danger due to its faulty design;
  (ii) Requirements: P must show a technologically and economically feasible alternative design or modification that would be safer as to the risk at issue;
(3) Inadequate warning:
  (i) Manufacturer fails to adequately warn of a non-obvious risk associated with a product's use;
  (ii) Includes duty to warn of foreseeable dangers from misuse;
  (iii) Requirements: P must show that the product failed to have clear and complete warnings of any dangers that would not have been ordinarily apparent to consumers;
  (iv) Unavoidably unsafe products: if a product cannot be made safe for its ordinary use (e.g., chain saw, firearms), manufacturer must give:
  (a) Proper instructions for use;
  (b) Adequate warnings of known dangers;
  (v) D is not liable for risks that were unforeseeable at the time the product was marketed.

