cards.backMarkdown:
Case 1: Decedent is survived by descendants who are also descendants of surviving spouse, and surviving spouse has no other descendants [Spouse + shared descendants]. Answer: Surviving spouse takes the entire estate;
Case 2: Decedent is survived by a parent but no descendant [Spouse + parent]. Answer: Surviving spouse takes $300,000 and 75% of the remainder of the estate;
Case 3: Decedent is survived by descendants who are also descendants of the surviving spouse, and the spouse has other issue [Spouse + shared descendants + spouse's kids]; Answer: Surviving spouse takes $225,000 and one half of the remaining property;
Example: Decedent dies owning $375,000 in property. She is survived by her Wife and their daughter, as well as her Wife's son by an earlier marriage. What is Wife's intestate share? Answer: $300,000.
Case 4: Decedent is survived by issue not related to the surviving spouse [Spouse + non-spousal kids]; Answer: Surviving spouse takes $150,000 and one-half of the remaining property.
Case 5: Decedent is not survived by descendants or parents [Just spouse]; Answer: Surviving spouse takes the entire estate. If no heirs, the property will escheat to the state.

