cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Requirements (document will be incorporated by reference where):
  (i) Intent to incorporate: the will manifests testator's intent to incorporate the document;
  (ii) Authenticated document: the will sufficiently describes the document such that it can be authenticated;
  (a) description must be such that the document can be reasonably identified, and
  (b) document must correspond to the will's description;
  (iii) In existence upon will execution (the document must be in existence at the time the will is executed).
(2) Tangible property exception: in most states, a will may incorporate by reference a document (i.e., statement or list) that disposes of testator's tangible personal property;
  (i) document can be prepared before or after execution of the will and can be changed before testator's death;
  (ii) Requirements: document must be
  (a) signed by testator, and
  (b) describe items and to whom they are devised with reasonable certainty.

