cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Requirement to pay obligations:
  (i) estate must always pay off obligations before distributing assets (i.e., satisfy debts, expenses, taxes, etc.);
  (ii) abatement occurs when, after doing so, the estate lacks sufficient funds to carry out disposition of property under terms of the will;
(2) Order of abatement:
  (i) Testator's will may set out an order of abatement;
  (ii) Absent provisions in the will, most state statutes provide for an order of abatement setting a priority as to which categories of property in the estate will be sold off first;
  (iii) Order (most states abate estate property in the following order):
  (a) Property not disposed of by will (i.e., passing by intestacy);
  (b) Residuary estate (i.e., the portion that would remain after all specific gifts and bequests have been made);
  (c) General devises (abate pro rata);
  (d) Specific devises and bequests.

