cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Inter vivos gift (a gift given by a living person to another living person):
  (i) Requirements (intent, delivery, and acceptance):
  (a) donor intends to make gift;
  (b) donor delivers gift (can be actual or constructive delivery);
  (c) donee accepts.
(2) Joint tenant bank account:
  (i) a surviving joint tenant is generally entitled to money in a jointly-held account when the other joint tenant dies;
  (ii) Usually arises where the account is in the name of two or more people with the "right of survivorship";
(3) Totten trust or POD ("Payable on Death") account:
  (i) Deposit of funds in one's own bank account held in trust for another (e.g., A opens account for herself as trustee for B);
  (ii) Creates a valid revocable trust, even though depositor has control;
  (iii) Funds pass to designated beneficiary upon trustee's death;
  (iv) Revocable by trustee-depositor by withdrawing funds before death or revoking the trust by will;
(4) Life insurance:
  (i) K made between policyholder and insurance company under which beneficiary is named;
  (ii) Unless K provides otherwise, policyholder cannot change the beneficiary through a provision in their will

