cards.backMarkdown:
(1) Executor:
  (i) one named in decedent's will to be the personal representative;
  (ii) No executor: if no executor is named in a will or decedent dies intestate, court appoints a personal representative (usually a surviving spouse or heir of decedent);
  (iii) Capacity: any person with the capacity to contract can be a personal representative (i.e., must be mentally competent and not a minor);
(2) Responsibilities:
  (i) generally, a representative/executor handles all matters associated with winding up decedent's estate;
  (ii) For Example: Filing paperwork, paying creditors, notifying beneficiaries and devisees, managing property distributions, etc.

